HEADWORD: Ekaluminium
<hw>Ek*al`u*min"i*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Skr.
<ets>⟦emac⟧ka</ets> one + E. <ets>aluminium</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The name given by <persfn>Mendeleev</persfn> to
a hypothetical element, -- later discovered and called
<altname>gallium</altname>. See <er>Gallium</er>, and cf.
<er>Ekabor</er>. Also see <cref>periodic table</cref>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

